text: Henry County is a county on the southeastern border of the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 17,146. The county seat is Abbeville. The county was named for Patrick Henry (1736â€“1799), famous orator and Governor of Virginia. Henry County was founded on December 13, 1819. == References == Category:1819 establishments in Alabama Category:Alabama counties
